==日本回應==
[[日本政府|日本政府]]一直強烈反對慰安妇少女铜像在領事館外豎立，但因銅像由非官方團體管有而非政府豎立，因此難以法律追究。

2015年12月，[[日本政府|日本政府]]表明不會支付十億日元作為賠償金，除非雕像從首爾的日本大使館前的位置被移除。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/southkorea/12075523/Comfort-women-statue-threatens-to-derail-Japan-South-Korea-accord.html |title= 'Comfort women' statue threatens to derail Japan-South Korea accord |publisher= [[Daily_Telegraph|Daily Telegraph]] |first1= MIke |last1= Firn |date= 31 Dec 2015 |accessdate= 23 April 2017 |archive-date= 2020-11-12 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031941/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/southkorea/12075523/Comfort-women-statue-threatens-to-derail-Japan-South-Korea-accord.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>2015年兩國政府達成協議。之後，韓國在[[釜山|釜山]]建立了第二座雕像。日本隨後召回兩名外交官，並停止雙方高層會談。<ref name="CNN Busan">{{cite web |url= http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/05/asia/south-korea-comfort-women-statue/ |title= Why this statue of a young girl caused a diplomatic incident |first1= Sol |last1= Han |first2= James |last2= Griffiths |date= 10 February 2017 |accessdate= 22 April 2017 |publisher= [[CNN|CNN]] |archive-date= 2021-03-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210308164240/https://www.cnn.com/2017/02/05/asia/south-korea-comfort-women-statue/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>

